BATTLE MOUNTAIN SP, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Battle Mountain SP, LLC ("Battle Mountain") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Battle Mountain generating facility ("Battle Mountain Facility").
The Battle Mountain Facility is a solar generating facility located in Humboldt County, Nevada. The Battle Mountain Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Sierra Pacific Power Company d/b/a NV Energy.
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Battle Mountain's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Battle Mountain Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission through March 10, 2022.
Battle Mountain's fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Reactive Service Revenue Requirement for the period January 20, 2022 through March 10, 2022 is: $83,013.70.
